/eq_view_profile.html?num=21119 " target="_blank"><Br><i>Pirv's Magelo Profile</i></a </p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/uheihache.showPublicProfile?language=EN>heihache</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Evoker</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/18/02 1:01:03 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=311.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.iquest.net/~jynx25/me.bmp WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duo quadding w/ a bard</span><hr size=1> My idea would be for the wizard to snare, you use autofollow and just play your dot constantly during combat while he burns them down.  Then just use mana song afterwards, although, I'm not very familair with your songs <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><center><img src="http://www.veeshanlol.com/images/hhtag.jpg" border=0></c></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ucuellar.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Cuellar</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/18/02 4:05:36 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=311.topic&index=2>Reply</a>    <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.battle.net/images/battle/diablo2/images/animations/bestiary/act1/Andariel.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duo quadding w/ a bard</span><hr size=1> I sit my bard with AOE mana song AFK on the other side of a zone line... then have my wizard go quad kite.  Pretty effective. ; )<br><br>Both classes can quad kite pretty well, but not together. You may want to consider an enchanter. They have their gravity flux for quad kiting, runes for avoiding damage, and c2.  Back when kunark first came out, I quad kited raptors with a druid somewhat well. <br><br>-Cuellar <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#33333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/ufirion69.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Firion69</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Apprentice</span><br> <font color=#ffffff>(2/19/02 10:35:08 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub23.ezboard.com/fgraffeswizardcompilationfrm20.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=311.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Duo quadding w/ a bard</span><hr size=1> assuming youre both good at positioning the mobs and you have pretty much space, have the wizzy aggro and snare the mobs  and then let him keep the aggro all the fight by having the wizzy between you and the mobs at all times so they have aggro on him and follow him, this can get tricky tho, esp. on raptor island.<br><br>Or assuming the bard songs range are limited and youre (the bard) good at keeping them in a bunch, let him bunch them and snare them, and keep the bard closest all the time, while the wizzy nukes the crap outta the mobs.<br><br>Why you wanna do this? I have found that even if i nuke mobs to half health and someone else just runs past who is KoS, the will split and follow the other person when i get too far away (further than the other person).<br><br>So the key is the range and positioning of you and the mob-bunch.<br><br>Regards, Firion <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right va